      "text": [
        " رَجُلٍ قَتَلَ رَجُلاً مُؤْمِناً قَالَ \"يُقَالُ لَهُ مُتْ أَيَّ مِيتَةٍ شِئْتَ يَهُودِيّاً وَ إِنْ شِئْتَ نَصْرَانِيّاً وَ إِنْ شِئْتَ مَجُوسِيّاً \"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.4962 - Ibn Abi Umayr narrated from Sa'id al-Azraq, from Abu Abdillah (as), regarding a man who killed a believing man.\nImam (as) said: \"It will be said to him, 'Die in any manner you wish, either as a Jew, or if you wish, as a Christian, or if you wish, as a Magian (Zoroastrian).'\""
        ]
      }
    },
